@MarcoFalke, that's right - can be removed from here too and should have been part of this PR, I missed it.

I missed it because in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21878 that "close listening sockets" code becomes unnecessary and is removed:

```diff
-    // Close listening sockets.
-    for (ListenSocket& hListenSocket : vhListenSocket) {
-        if (hListenSocket.socket != INVALID_SOCKET) {
-            if (!CloseSocket(hListenSocket.socket)) {
-                LogPrintf("CloseSocket(hListenSocket) failed with error %s\n", NetworkErrorString(WSAG
-            }
-        }
-    }
```

This removal is also in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21879 which is chopped off from the big https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21878 to ease review.

I will leave it as is to avoid further conflicts, hoping that https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21879 will eventually make it in.
